=== Query 1: What are the laws for a minor? ===
[Smart Match] Offline dictionary invoked for context_user_1774500415458
Source: knowledge
Response:\nCrimes against anyone under 18 (minors) are strictly dealt with under the POCSO (Protection of Children from Sexual Offences) Act or Juvenile Justice Act.

• Punishments under POCSO are far more severe than standard IPC crimes.
• Bail is exceptionally difficult and strictly evaluated by special courts.
• The identity of the minor is legally protected and must never be disclosed.

Please consult a specialized lawyer or approach your nearest District Legal Services Authority immediately. \n\n
=== Query 2: And how long is the bail time for that? ===
[Smart Match] Offline dictionary invoked for context_user_1774500415458
Source: knowledge
Response:\nBail is the temporary release of an accused person awaiting trial. The approval time depends on the type of offence (bailable/non-bailable), court workload, and case complexity. Usually it can take from a few hours to a few days. \n\n
=== Query 3: What about a murder scenario? ===
[Smart Match] Offline dictionary invoked for context_user_1774500415458
Source: knowledge
Response:\nSection 302 of the IPC prescribes the punishment for murder, which may include the death penalty or life imprisonment. Bail is generally not granted by lower courts. \n\n
